==影响和争议==
“年度新声”的获选艺人往往能在下一年获得成功，这项评选也因此吸引了广泛的关注，但与此同时也引发了一定的争议。曾经参加过“2008年度新声”投票的《[[卫报|卫报]]》评论家凯蒂·安帕尔（{{lang|en|Kitty Empire}}）就曾在2007年12月指出，“年度新声”的投票人与[[全英音乐奖|全英音乐奖]]“评论家选择奖”高度重合，而其中很多人自己便是音乐媒体的记者和编辑，他们自己会写乐评和预测，评选因此更像是一种[[自证预言|自证预言]]。<ref>{{cite news  | title = Tipping the sound of 2008  | publisher = [[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]  | date = 2007-12-07  | url = http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/musicblog/2007/dec/09/tippingthesoundof2008  | accessdate = 2014-10-31  | location = London  | first = Kitty  | last = Empire  | archive-date = 2012-05-18  | archive-url = https://www.webcitation.org/67kUPafcN?url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/musicblog/2007/dec/09/tippingthesoundof2008  | dead-url = no  }}</ref>

2011年，在“2012年度新声”的15人提名公布之后，《[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]》评论人乔·伯吉斯（{{lang|en|Joe Burgis}}）指出,“2012年度新声”的提名中仅有两位[[独立音乐|独立音乐人]]，过于偏爱主流艺人。<ref name = "Telegraph">{{cite news  | title = BBC's Sound of 2012 list favours mainstream acts  | publisher = [[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Telegraph]]  | date = 2011-12-06  | url = http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/music-news/8935687/BBCs-Sound-of-2012-list-favours-mainstream-acts.html  | accessdate = 2014-10-31  | location = London  | first = Joe  | last = Burgis  | archive-date = 2014-10-31  | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141031150525/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/music-news/8935687/BBCs-Sound-of-2012-list-favours-mainstream-acts.html  | dead-url = no  }}</ref>{{link-en|独立音乐协会|Association of Independent Music}}主席艾莉森·温汉姆（{{lang|en|Alison Wenham}}）也对这一年的提名提出不满，称其“和音乐没什么关系”，“完全没有意义”。她在接受《[[新音乐快递|新音乐快递]]》杂志采访时还表示，过去几年已经证明这项投票活动“并不准确”。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/various-artists/60816|title=BBC Sound Of 2012 list is 'completely meaningless', says Association of Independent Music chairman|work=[[NME|NME]]|date=2011-12-06|accessdate=2014-10-31|archive-date=2014-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031143907/http://www.nme.com/news/various-artists/60816|dead-url=no}}</ref>

针对这些负面评价，[[BBC廣播一台|BBC廣播一台]]和{{link-en|BBC广播1Xtra台|BBC Radio 1Xtra|1Xtra}}的负责人乔治·埃尔加托迪斯（{{lang|en|George Ergatoudis}}）回应称，“这份提名必然会引发争议，但重要的是，它能使人们从越来越广大的人群中发现更多努力的优秀歌手和艺术家，这一定是一件好事。”<ref name = "Telegraph"/>

